Package: earthquake
Title: Visualization of NOAA earthquake data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Chunlei", "Zheng", email = "zhengcl75@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: The earthquake package is to facilitate exploration of NOAA earthquake data. It mainly provides
             two functionalities. One is to visualize the earthquake information in a timeline format, 
             given a time span of countries. Another is to visualize these information in an interactive map.
Depends: R (>= 3.4.0)
Imports: ggplot2, dplyr, tidyr, leaflet, lubridate, readr, testthat
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.1.0
Suggests: knitr,
    rmarkdown
VignetteBuilder: knitr
